The largest ivory seizure since the 1989 ban on the trade was made from a shipment from Malawi bound for the Far East, representing ivory from thousands of elephants.
The situation is dire, with elephants facing extinction unless strong enforcement is reinstated.
DNA testing has helped identify the origin of poached tusks, aiding in curbing the illegal ivory trade.
Various countries are proposing bans on ivory trade, while conservation efforts are underway to protect elephants and other wildlife.
The need for sustainable management practices is crucial to ensure the survival of these majestic creatures.
